===Adjective===
'''acute''' ({{compar}} '''more acute''', {{superl}} '''most acute''')

#[[Urgent]].
#:''his need for medical attention was '''acute'''''
#[[Intense]].
#:''She had an '''acute''' sense of honor''
#:''Eagles have very '''acute''' vision.''
#{{geometry}} Of an angle, less than 90 degrees.
#{{geometry}} Of a triangle, [[acute-angled]].
#{{medicine}} Of an abnormal [[condition]] of recent or sudden [[onset]]; this sense does not imply severity (unlike the common usage).
#:'''''acute''' angina''
#''See'' '''[[acute accent]]'''
#(''after the noun'') Of a letter, having an acute accent.
#:''The last letter of "café" is 'e' acute.''

